{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nFor an additive map the two signers must write distinct, self-identifying keys, and\ncompletion validity needs a material fingerprint to detect post-signing edits.\n## What\nBoth sign sites set an unsigned `data[\"kind\"]` on the `SIGNATURE` event (`plan-review`,\n`completion-verifier`) for robust routing (kind stays anchored via `manifest[0]`). The\ncompletion signer ALSO records the plan-review material fingerprint\n(description/AC/file_impact/children) as a manifest line, so completion validity-on-read can\nrecompute and compare (symmetric with plan-review). Drift-refresh re-sign preserves kind.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py` (`sign_plan_review`, `refresh_attestation`),\n`src/rebar/_commands/transition.py` (`_verdict_manifest` + completion signing),\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (kind passthrough if needed).\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Plan-review SIGNATURE events carry `data[\"kind\"]==\"plan-review\"`.\n- [ ] Completion SIGNATURE events carry `data[\"kind\"]==\"completion-verifier\"`.\n- [ ] Completion manifest records the material fingerprint (legacy completion sigs without it are treated as material-unknown by validity-on-read).\n- [ ] `data[\"kind\"]` and the fingerprint line do NOT alter the existing canonical payload in a way that breaks old signatures (no PAYLOAD_VERSION bump).\n- [ ] Drift-refresh re-sign preserves the same kind.\n## Added (review)\n- The completion signer computes the material fingerprint via the SAME helper plan-review\n  uses (single source of the material field set); it does not redefine the field list."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782785063116569001,"uuid":"c30e1d29-6de5-432e-b3a7-78ab9fc64e82"}